      "notes": {
        "patternRationale": "Strangler migrations reduce cutover risk by routing slices of capability to new services while preserving controlled coexistence with legacy systems.",
        "onboardingQuestions": "Ask which legacy boundary is being strangled, what facade controls traffic, what replacement runtime will host new code, and how data synchronization and rollback are handled."
      },
