      "description": "Shared Amazon ECS Fargate cluster that hosts every product's containerized\nAPI and worker services (Coverage, TimePay, Talent, People APIs; the\nIdentity Gateway; the Talent background-check Celery worker). Surfaced\nlate in this exercise: the Phase 2 inferred shared-services list\n(identity, observability, data platform, messaging, CI/CD, secrets,\nAPI gateway) did not originally include a generic compute/container\nsubstrate, and the gap only became visible once Phase 5 needed a\nconcrete RuntimeService UID for each SDP's serviceGroup.substrate field.\nLogged as a friction point: SDP construction is itself an effective way\nto surface missing shared-services inventory that a Phase-2-style\nup-front brainstorm can miss.\n",
